The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Thursday, October 23, 2003 				 Set-top regime
																								Lucknow, Oct. 22 (PTI): Union minister of state for information and broadcasting Ravi Shankar Prasad today said the conditional access system (CAS) would be implemented in a state only on the recommendation of the chief minister. 																								On implementation of CAS in Delhi, the minister said since it had become a poll issue, it would be put in place only after the elections.  MTNL rate slash																								Mahanagar Telephone Nigam Ltd will slash call rates to the US and Europe by 40 per cent for a month. 																								The new tariff will be a flat rate of Rs 14.40 per minute, all days of the week, effective from the midnight of October 23-24, the company has said in a statement in New Delhi.
